HEADWORD: Abelonian
<hw>A`bel*o"ni*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a sect in Africa (4th
century), mentioned by St. Augustine, who states that they married, but
lived in continence, after the manner, as they pretended, of
Abel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

